Reference-contexts: A working prototype of an outward-looking system was built by Jih-Fang Wang, which used a configuration of three cameras tracked beneath a ceiling equipped with infrared 1 LEDs [WANG90]. Following that success, a full-scale operational tracking system was designed and built at UNC <ref> [WARD92] </ref>. There are many potential sources of noise and systematic error in this outward-looking system. There is electrical noise and quantization noise in the digital sampling of the camera data. There is numerical error introduced in the processing of that data by the position recovery algorithm (PRA) [AZUM91].
